.SH "NAME"
tang-nagios \- A Nagios plugin for Tang
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBtang\fR \-u URL
.SH "OVERVIEW"
.sp
This Nagios plugin for Tang enables Nagios to monitor a Tang server for its basic functionality as well as performance metrics\&. The plugin is executed simply by providing the base URL to the Tang service\&.
.sp
The plugin will test the following functionality:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP "  1." 4.2
.\}
Downloading the advertisement\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP "  2." 4.2
.\}
Verification of advertisement semantics\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 3.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP "  3." 4.2
.\}
Verification of signatures for all advertised signing keys\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04' 4.\h'+01'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP "  4." 4.2
.\}
Verification of key exchanges for all advertised exchange keys\&.
.RE
.sp
If any of these tests fail, an error will be generated\&. Upon success, the plugin will output the following performance metrics:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBadv\fR
: Time it took to fetch the advertisement (in μs)\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBexc\fR
: Average time of all key exchange operations (in μs)\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBnkeys\fR
: Number of keys in the advertisement\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBnsigk\fR
: Number of signing keys in the advertisement\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\fBnexck\fR
: Number of exchange keys in the advertisement\&.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
A simple test against a localhost Tang server:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
$ \&./tang \-u http://localhost/
OK|adv=21430 exc=44587 nkeys=2 nsigk=1 nexck=1
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
